        The Eastern Collegiate Athletic Conference unveiled the nations 
first intercollegiate womens ice hockey league and announced the 12 teams 
will begin play in the 199394 season The top eight finishers in the ECAC 
Womens Ice Hockey League will qualify for a postseason tournament The 
league replaces an informal 15team conference of nine Division I and six 
Division III schools which held their own respective division tournaments 
at the end of the regular season The ECAC said it would discontinue its 
Division III womens tournament after the 199293 season

